        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 4:26PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
J B Thomas Reservoir, or 15 miles southeast of Gail, moving north at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fluvanna, J B Thomas Reservoir, and Knapp.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
